Use the [try-catch.ts](mdc:utils/try-catch.ts) utility for better error catching and management. For example:

```ts
// Example 1
const captchaResult = await tryCatch(verifyHCaptchaToken(hcaptchaToken));

const sessionResult = await tryCatch(
  stripe.checkout.sessions.create({
    line_items: [{ price: form.stripe.priceId, quantity: 1 }],
    mode: "payment",
    success_url: `${baseUrl}/forms/${formSlug}?paymentStatus=success`,
    cancel_url: `${baseUrl}/forms/${formSlug}`,
    metadata: {
      formId: form._id,
      recordId,
    },
  }),
);

// Example 2
const parsedInput = tryCatch(() => submitFormSchema.parse(input));

// Example 3
const priceResult = await tryCatch(getPrice(form.stripe.priceId));

if (priceResult.error) {
  console.error(priceResult.error);
  return notFound();
}

const price = priceResult.data;
```

Use the utility whenever a function is likely to throw an error.